Nigeria will host the second leg of their 2022 FIFA World Cup playoff against Ghana. The game will be played at the Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja on Tuesday. Over the two legs, only one of the West African rivals will get the chance to clinch one of the five spots available for the continent at the tournament later this year. Both teams played out a goalless draw in the first leg last Friday, unable to cancel each other out in Kumasi. However, a winner must emerge when they face each other again four days later. Kick off will be 6pm Nigerian time. Nigeria XI vs Ghana: Uzoho; Balogun, Troost-Ekong, Bassey, Aina; Etebo, Onyeka, Aribo; Dennis, Lookman, Osimhen. Tuesday, March 29
First half: Troost-Ekong’s penalty has cancelled out Partey’s opener. Half time. Second half: Full time: